<Base title="Chan Beng Chung">
  <h1>Hey, I'm Beng Chung.</h1>

  <p>
    Created this website to have a little digital footprint of myself and a little diary of what I have explored.
  </p>

  <h2>How it started</h2>

  <p>
    My colleague was leaving the firm for better opportunities. I was bored one day and decided to copy his domain name — just changed the letter "P" to "B".
  </p>

  <p>
    So I forked his kopi ordering website. Took a look at his code and it was quite straightforward. The unique part was how he stored orders and let other users view the same data in real time. Not overly complex, but it got the job done.
  </p>

  <h2>Falling in love with Cloudflare</h2>

  <p>
    When it came to hosting, I used Cloudflare — and I fell in love with it. Linking GitHub, setting up key-value storage, domain routing. Simple enough that it feels like anybody can do it too.
  </p>

  <h2>Now</h2>

  <p>
    And after that began my journey of vibe coding.
  </p>
</Base>
